## HEADING HIERARCHY (enforced)
- Exactly ONE h1 per page (in hero)
- h2 for major section titles
- h3 for subsections
- h4 for card titles and spec labels
- Never skip levels

## INTERNAL LINKING RULES
- Every page links to 3+ other internal pages
- Guide links to all category pages
- AI/ML links to guide, lidar, drones, news
- Every category page links to guide and financing
- Financing links back to guide
- Descriptive anchor text — never "click here"
- Breadcrumbs on all pages except index (BreadcrumbList schema)

## AI / LLM OPTIMIZATION
- Open every educational section with a direct answer to the implied question
- Use question-answer format in FAQ sections with details/summary elements
- semantic HTML throughout: main, article, section, aside, nav
- Schema FAQPage on guide and category pages
- Clear, authoritative sentences — AI assistants surface direct answers


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 4 — FINANCING FORM SPECIFICATION
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

This is NOT a purchase form. It collects interest from users who want
help finding financing for surveying equipment.

Page hero:
  Kicker: "Take the Next Step"
  H1: "Equipment Financing — Let's Talk"
  Subtext: "We don't sell equipment — but we connect interested buyers with
  financing partners. Tell us what you're looking at and we'll be in touch."

Form uses div.financing-form NOT a form tag. Submit via JS fetch.

Fields:
  Group 1 — About You:
    Full Name (required), Email (required), Phone, Company, Job Title,
    State/Region (required, select all US states + International)

  Group 2 — Your Project:
    Project Type (required, select), Project Scale (select), Timeline (select)

  Group 3 — Equipment Interest:
    Equipment Categories (required, multi-checkbox: LiDAR Systems / Survey
    Drones / GNSS-RTK / Total Stations / Terrestrial Scanners / Mobile
    Mapping Systems / Field Computers & Software / Sensors & Camera Payloads)
    Budget Range (required, select), Specific Equipment in Mind (textarea),
    Additional Notes (textarea)

  Group 4 — Consent:
    Checkbox: I agree to be contacted (required)
    Checkbox: I understand this is an educational site, not a direct retailer (required)

Submit behavior:
  - Validate all required fields first
  - Highlight missing fields with border-color var(--accent)
  - On success: replace form with success message in same panel
  - Success: "Thank you, [Name]. We've received your interest and will be in touch within 2 business days."
  - Endpoint: const FORM_ENDPOINT = 'https://formspree.io/f/YOUR_FORM_ID'

Form styling:
  - Background: var(--surface)
  - Labels: Barlow Condensed 11px uppercase letter-spacing 3px color var(--muted)
  - Inputs: background var(--surface2), border 1px solid var(--border), color var(--white)
  - Focus: border-color var(--accent), outline none
  - Two columns desktop, single column mobile
  - Required asterisk in accent color


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 5 — AI/ML PAGE STRUCTURE (pages/ai-ml.html)
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Hero:
  Kicker: "The Intelligent Field"
  H1: "Machine Learning is Reshaping Geospatial Work"
  Side text: "GeoAI & Automation"

Section 01 — LiDAR Automation:
  Kicker: "Point Cloud Intelligence"
  H2: "How AI classifies 6 billion points overnight"
  Cover: Deep learning models (KPConv, PointNet++), 95%+ accuracy,
  workflow steps, tools: LP360 AI, TerraSolid AutoClass, Lidarvisor cloud,
  Global Mapper Pro ML

Section 02 — Photogrammetry Automation:
  Kicker: "Semantic Photogrammetry"
  H2: "From photos to 3D models without the manual grind"
  Cover: Pix4D semantic photogrammetry, intersection tie points, SAM
  integration, auto GCP detection, GPU acceleration
  Tools: Pix4Dmatic, Metashape, RealityCapture, OpenDroneMap

Section 03 — GeoAI:
  Kicker: "Spatial Intelligence"
  H2: "Teaching machines to understand geography"
  Cover: Automated feature extraction, predictive infrastructure
  maintenance, change detection, semantic segmentation
  Tools: ArcGIS AI, QGIS deepness, GeoAI Python, Google Earth Engine, Mach9

Tools Matrix:
  Table comparing 9 tools: what it automates, skill required, cost tier

FAQ Section (6 questions using details/summary):
  1. Will AI replace surveyors?
  2. How accurate is automated LiDAR classification?
  3. Do I need coding skills?
  4. AI vs traditional automated processing?
  5. Can AI process any LiDAR sensor data?
  6. How does Gaussian Splatting differ from photogrammetry?

CTAs: Link to financing form and guide quiz


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 6 — ANIMATIONS
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Use Intersection Observer in animations.js:
  - .reveal elements start at opacity:0 translateY(24px)
  - Transition to opacity:1 translateY(0) in 0.6s ease when visible
  - Stagger children with 100ms delay increments
  - .count-up triggers number animation when visible
  - Hero content animates on page load, not scroll
  - Card borders brighten to --border-mid on hover
  - Read More underlines draw in via CSS width transition


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 7 — NEVER DO LIST
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Never use white or light backgrounds
Never use colors outside the defined palette
Never use gradients on background surfaces
Never use box-shadows decoratively
Never use font-weight 700+ on Barlow (only Playfair Display)
Never use rounded corners over 4px
Never use form tags — always div with JS handlers
Never claim the site sells equipment
Never put a price without context
Never use Inter, Roboto, Arial, or system fonts
Never use purple gradients or generic AI startup aesthetic
Never skip heading levels
Never use alert() confirm() or prompt()
Never use localStorage
Never write inline event handlers onclick= — use addEventListener
Never add a page without full SEO meta tags


