# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## Page: pages/start-a-company.html

Title: How to Start a Land Surveying Company — Licenses, Costs & Revenue | GeoSurveyHub
Description: Complete guide to starting a surveying company: PS license path, NCEES exams, startup costs ($45K–$250K), revenue potential, and what it really takes to go independent.
Primary Keyword: how to start a land surveying company
Schema: HowTo + FAQPage

## Hero
Kicker: "Your Own Firm"
H1: "How to Start a *Surveying Company*"
Subtext: "The license you need, what it really costs, how much you can make, and the honest path from technician to firm owner."
Side text: "Entrepreneur's Guide"
Stats row: 8 years (typical path to PS license) / $45K–$250K (typical startup cost) / 25–30% (top firm net margin)

## Page Sections (MNTN numbered layout)
01 — The Opportunity: Market size, talent shortage, why now is the right time
02 — Getting Licensed: FS exam → supervised experience → PS exam → state exam. Full timeline.
03 — Business Formation: LLC vs PC, registrations, insurance requirements
04 — Startup Costs: Tiered tables (solo / small crew / tech-forward). Honest numbers.
05 — Revenue Potential: Pricing by survey type, revenue scenarios, profit benchmarks
06 — Year One Roadmap: Month-by-month checklist as a visual workflow
07 — Common Mistakes: 6 mistakes as a styled warning list
08 — Key Organizations: NCEES / NSPS / ASPRS / ACSM / State Associations

## Special Components
License Path Visual: SVG timeline showing FS → Experience → PS → State Exam → License
Pricing Table: Survey type / typical price range / notes — comparison-table class
Revenue Scenarios: Info cards with count-up numbers (stat cards)
Year One Roadmap: workflow-steps component
FAQ Section (6 items with details/summary accordion):
  1. Do I need a surveying degree to get licensed?
  2. Can I start a surveying company if I'm not licensed myself?
  3. How much does E&O insurance cost for a new surveying firm?
  4. How do I find my first clients as a new surveying company?
  5. What is the difference between FS and PS exams?
  6. How long until a surveying company becomes profitable?

